[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]The chart below compares the number of new cases of syphilis, gonorrhoea, herpes, and genital warts in England and Wales per thousand members of the population.  The comparison is limited to these STIs because there was no HIV/AIDS in the 1950s, and no records were kept of 
[normal]chlamydia
[normal] or other infections.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]1955 
[normal]|                           |
[normal] 0.7
[normal]2004 
